title: For Sale:  Vintage Police Package of S&W 10-5 revolver, Jay-Pee holster, Bianchi belt, extra grips
postcontent: As I near the end of the sell off of my guns, this is a unique opportunity to own the gun, holster, and belt used by a police officer in New Jersey. This police package came from an estate sale.  The revolver is a 1968 model Smith & Wesson Model blued 10-5 that shows "character" and wears it with pride! This was the everyday carry weapon for this police officer until his retirement many years ago. Bore and cylinder are clean and everything feels tight. The rear sights and front ramp have white paint lightly dabbed on for the "old school" edition of fiber optic sights we have today.  The revolver has lots of holster wear and some light freckling in a few spots, but I think it is in better aesthetic condition than I would have expected from a career long everyday use and carry gun. This gun has not been abused, as this is just honest wear from being on the job for many years. There is wear primarily on the inside corners where they rubbed while in the holster, but there is also much evidence externally of it being a true "on the job" weapon. Bore and chambers on the cylinder are good and have been well maintained. After all, this officer's life depended on this gun working every time he might have to pull the trigger.  The gun came to me with beautiful custom-made dark walnut with target thumb rest grips. I will include them in the sale, but the buyer has their choice of an additional pair of either Smith & Wesson wood grips or rubber Pachmayr Gripper grips. I have attached pics of the gun with the original target grips, as well as pics of both options to help you decide which of the two bonus options you prefer.  I had the gun's side plate off and completely cleaned while intact the internals, then oiled them before replacing the side plate. That helped improve an already smooth trigger and added to the accuracy of the gun.  The holster is a Jay-Pee Spring Lock Safety Swivel Holster that features a trigger guard click retention button to keep the pistol securely inside the holster until it can easily be removed with a push of the finger as you draw the pistol. It also has space on the belt to hold a dozen .38 Special bullets. The belt is a Bianchi 42 with adjustable sizing and quick connection prongs.  This is a really cool police package that will easily take you back in time to when this officer carried his gun with this belt and holster.  Local face-to-face cash sale only. Buyer must be at least 21, Oklahoma resident able to legally buy a firearm in Oklahoma, and must have a current valid Oklahoma issued picture ID. No exceptions.  $295 for the entire package. Please contact me if you would like to see the belt and holster pic and other pictures I have available.
